Sprinkle chicken with curry powder and cayenne pepper. Cook chicken with 1 tablespoon margarine in large skillet over medium heat 5 to 6 minutes on each side or until browned. Remove from skillet; set aside. Cook and stir carrots with remaining tablespoons margarine in same skillet 2 minutes. Add 1-1/4 cups water, milk, pasta, Special Seasonings packet and raisins. Stir and bring to a boil. Place chicken over pasta. Return to a boil. Reduce heat to medium. Gently boil uncovered 5 to 6 minutes or until pasta is tender and chicken is no longer pink in center, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with cilantro.